import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].mean(), color='red', label='mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(x=data['delay'].median(), color='green', label='median: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = 1
    df = data.groupby(['origin', 'destination']).count().reset_index()
    df = df.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False).head(10)
    chart = sns.barplot(x='count', y='origin', hue='destination', data=df)
    chart.set_title('Which airports have the highest number of flights?')
    chart.axvline(df['count'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Max: {df['count'].max():.2f}")
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
